##Affecting the whole body: Small and medium-sized enterprises to resume work road

Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

Return to work is not a simple recall of staff, in addition to staff return to work, epidemic prevention, transportation, orders, manpower, supply chain are factors need to be considered, affecting the whole body. The formation of a complete industrial chain in the manufacturing center, but also let the local resumption of a comprehensive project.

Reporter | Huang Ziyi

Back to work

Return to work is not a simple recall of staff, in addition to staff return to work, epidemic prevention, transportation, orders, manpower, supply chain are factors need to be considered, affecting the whole body. The formation of a complete industrial chain in the manufacturing center, but also let the local resumption of a comprehensive project.

Reporter | Huang Ziyi

Back to work

▲▲▲

Back to work

▲▲▲

On January 11,2020, Zeng Wuxiang, the 56-year-old owner of Dongguan Gerui furniture factory, launched a circle of friends. In the photo, piles of packaged goods line the doorway of his two-story, 3,000-square-meter factory building. A 15-metre semi-trailer with the letters printed on it is parked at the entrance of the factory, waiting for forklifts and workers to load the cartons, which will be shipped to the European and American markets with curved wooden tables and chairs.

This was Tseng wu-hsiang's last shipment years ago. After doing this, the furniture factory will enter the Spring Festival holiday, more than 40 workers almost all went home, Zeng Wuxiang also drove from Dongguan to Ji'an home. If no accident, in accordance with the laws of the Pearl River Delta in previous years, around the 10th day of the first lunar month, workers will return to work in an orderly manner. "No later than the Lantern Festival, " Zeng said.

The sudden outbreak has changed the rhythm of the decade. Until the day of the interview on February 20, Zeng's factory had not been able to resume work. Now nearly half a month after the Lantern Festival, he lives and eats in the factory area every day, occasionally relying on sleep to pass the time. "I am in self-isolation now, how do you know where the people outside come from? " Zeng Wuxiang told me. Dongguan now return to the gradual increase in personnel, he is afraid of the risk of infection, try not to leave the factory area.

The factory can not do without Zeng Wuxiang. As the epidemic spread, he realized the seriousness of the situation and drove back to Dongguan the day before his hometown, Fengcun. In mid-february, the furniture factory in Dalingshan, Dongguan News can resume work, provided that the epidemic prevention, through inspection. So, Ceng Wuxiang finished to resume work application materials, these materials to the factory industrial park in the village, and then the village to the town, the town can be inspected after the start. To this end, Ceng Wuxiang spent thousands of yuan, will more than a month ago also filled with factory goods workshop, placed on the 6 cases of 84 disinfectant.

February 10 is the time set by Guangdong Province to resume work, with 4,491 companies in Dongguan, the "factory of the world" , of which 80 per cent are manufacturers, many of them qualified to produce medical supplies. Dongguan Municipal Bureau of social, resumption of work to take batch process, step by step, "resumption of work is not rushed to all in place. ". As of February 20, Zeng had not yet been able to resume work in the park, he said: "everyone is waiting for the inspection. "

These inspections include the "four in place" , namely the prevention and Control Mechanism, the staff investigation, the facilities and materials, and the internal management, as well as the "eight ones" , for each employee to achieve health testing, temperature, wearing masks, set up isolation observation room eight items, but also requested to hold a staff safety meeting and take photos for evidence. Zeng Wuxiang will be the factory dormitory top floor vacated 5 ~ 6 houses, made a special isolation area. "We have masks because we usually make furniture, and there are thousands of industrial masks in our warehouse, " Zeng said. On Feb. 21, when people from the town checked and agreed to go back to work, a stone fell from his heart and he quickly notified scattered employees to go back to the factory.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As of February 21, the resumption rate in Shandong, Zhejiang, Jiangsu, Fujian and other east China areas exceeded 70 percent.

The outbreak has shut down businesses across the country. No matter which industry, from stagnation to recovery, is not an easy thing, a very important reason is that anti-epidemic materials can not be put in place. "materials are really hard to buy, " said the head of an Internet company in Chengdu. They have been seeking various materials since early February, "racking their brains and trying all kinds of channels. " Even after hearing that byd was going to make masks, he contacted the company and was told they were not for sale. In the end, under the coordination of the government, they purchased a reserve of 10,000 masks from various overseas sources. At the rate of two per employee per day, the supplies could sustain a company of 180 people for a month. By the time we got the supplies, the start date was pushed back another week.

The greater difficulty is the shortage of hands. Zeng Wuxiang hired workers from Jiangxi, Hubei, Hunan and other places, the epidemic is serious, the local village road closure, it is difficult to say whether back. He has put Hubei and Jiangxi Jiujiang employees on hold, saying they "will not return anyway" . In order to solve the problem of shortage of human resources in the process of resuming work, many places such as Guangdong, Zhejiang, Fujian and Jiangsu have opened point-to-point special train services or even chartered flights to transport manpower for workers returning to work in large enterprises, staged an alternative "people-snatching war. ".

For example, from Feb. 16, the city of Huzhou, Zhejiang Province, returned 16,000 workers in 48 hours, including 3,000 new hires, to receive a one-time living allowance of 1,000 yuan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In order to ease the difficulty of employing people, many places sent special planes to pick up workers (photo taken on February 18) 

The most difficult part of the process is getting workers out of the villages, says the head of a staffing company that helps the Huzhou government charter flights to attract talent. The government bears all the costs of the charter flights, but the money is well spent: In the Spring and Autumn Period, the price of a charter flight from Kunming to Shanghai is 460,000 yuan, "The bureau [ the leaders ] did an accounting, and the company lost one million yuan a day if the staff didn't arrive. ".

However, these charter flights, mostly concentrated in the local government-supported large and medium-sized enterprises, small enterprises have little opportunity to enjoy. Even as he slowly returned to work, Zeng said, he was anxious: he had to pay 70,000 yuan a month in rent to support 40 workers, and he had purchased 300,000 yuan of imported timber raw materials a year ago to start a big job later this year, but there are few orders upstream at the moment.

"So I still can not work ah! " Zeng Wuxiang said, furniture factory usually mainly responsible for processing bentwood furniture, upstream enterprises have other furniture factory, foreign trade companies. The head of a Foreign Trade Company told me, they are also very few orders, mainly overseas customers to consider the impact of the epidemic and did not order. Today, Zeng Wuxiang Account can reserve less than 150,000 yuan of funds, it has been difficult to pay full wages to employees, "otherwise I may not insist on a month. ".

"The key is to move first. "

▲▲▲

"The key is to move first. "

The economy is stagnant, as is the flow of logistics data, and the Internet companies involved. Kaijing technology is a digital freight platform operating "Zebra to pull" technology enterprises. Since its founding in 2015, the company has nearly doubled its annual sales, and in the past three years it has received a total of 1.2 billion yuan in three rounds of financing from investors including Ant Financial and sequoia capital. By 2020, the company had set a goal of doubling its sales in the first quarter of this year. On January 31st Lu Yang, the company's senior vice president, looked behind the scenes and saw a 10% year on year performance.

A total of 20,000 small and medium-sized logistics enterprises were connected on the cargo platform of Kejing technology. During the epidemic period, except for the sporadic delivery of medical supplies, the rest of the transport capacity was almost zero. A lot of investors called that day, asking about the impact of the epidemic. Lu said that every year after the Spring Festival is the peak season of the logistics industry. After February 10, the logistics enterprises on the platform gradually showed signs of resuming work, but only 20% to 30% of their normal transportation capacity, focusing on the fast-selling, fresh, medical and other industries in the province. One of their biggest partners in Shanghai expects its first quarter revenues to fall by nearly 50 million yuan. "Rent, labor costs, these, eyes open and shut, a day may be two million consumption out, no matter how big logistics companies can withstand, " Lu said.

When conventional production shuts down, some businesses survive by starting to produce medical supplies. In Dongguan, many companies have switched to making face masks and disinfectants, while in Wenzhou, in Zhejiang Province, the worst affected area outside Hubei, many garment factory workers have been working nonstop since February. Li Boqin, chairman of Wenzhou Aile Clothing Co. , told me that after the epidemic spread, the Wenzhou government called a meeting of the major associations to call for the production of medical supplies and to solve the problems of masks, isolation clothes and protective clothing. About 20 to 30 companies, including Li Boqin, signed up on the spot.

Li Boqin's company specializes in high-end apparel, mainly for the overseas market. Garment production is basically done by hand by workers, there are nearly 200 workers, but only 10 to 20 workers left over for the Spring Festival. Lee Boqin said, because the workers are not in place, the production of masks, input and output, compared to normal is "very small. ". "If the machine could make 100,000 masks a day, it could only make 3,000 to 5,000 now, " said Li, who said the masks were made of nanomaterials and could be used for two or three days.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Special period, the countermeasure of a few enterprises is to change production face mask, protective clothing and other medical supplies.

Before the Spring Festival, Li Boqin bought valuable overseas raw materials, and now backlog in the warehouse, because of the decline in overseas orders. "A lot of clients overseas are very risk-aware, " said Li Boqin, who said that when the epidemic first spread, many of his clients in the United States and Europe sent emails and called every day to ask, and all he could tell them was that it was under control. According to his estimates, it could take early March for Wenzhou to recover gradually, more than 20 days less than in a normal year. "The garment industry is very seasonal, and these 20 days mean we basically have no income from the spring collection until tomorrow, " Li said. "On the surface, it looks like we missed 20 days, but we missed a whole year. "

It was a difficult time for Li Boqin that he had never experienced in his career. He founded aile clothing in 2008, in the fierce competition in the high-end clothing market to find their own positioning, but also to some international well-known brands to do oem, is the ingenuity of Wenzhou Clothing Chamber of Commerce Manufacturing Enterprises, annual output value of about 30 million yuan. But since the 2018 trade war between China and the United States, output has fallen by about 30 percent, and now he estimates it will drop to 50 percent to 60 percent as the epidemic intensifies.

"because customers are risk-averse, " said Li Boqin, usually an overseas order, they receive the order after 3 to 4 months delivery, customers to consider the risk control during this period, in case the retail side "skylight. ". Beginning in the 2018 sino-us trade war, customers began passing some orders on to other manufacturers to spread the risk. "like an egg in a basket, when they take a little bit out and put it in another egg basket, our orders are reduced, " said Liebertchen, so he has to move first, even if it's just to produce masks, "If a client sees you shut down today and shut down tomorrow, confidence will be shaken. The key is to get moving first. "

Epidemic Prevention workers prepare to board a plane to take the body temperature of workers returning to the airport in Taizhou, Zhejiang Province, on Feb. 22.

More importantly, their first move in order to drive the industry supply chain supporting the project to move. "I can't move unless I move my suppliers, otherwise he would think I might change my suppliers, " said Li Boqin, who said the situation was obvious in a place like Wenzhou, where light industry is well developed, the local clothing, leather, auto accessories and so on have accumulated a deep industrial foundation in many years of development, the supporting system is very developed ———————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————— Industrial Chain needs upstream and downstream cooperation in order to gradually resume work and even full capacity. "If the suppliers can't move, even if I have 99 out of 100 processes, if I can't do one, I still can't get back to work, " said Lee, who said the factory still has a backlog of goods, just one last process to complete.

Made in China is just like this, never refers to a specific enterprise or industry, but refers to a complete, mature industrial chain, with extremely strong upstream and downstream supporting capacity, each other fine division of labor, interlocking finished products. Once the chain is down, no one's safe. With such a mature industrial chain, garment manufacturing costs in Wenzhou are generally lower than elsewhere, so overseas customers are willing to come, Li said. "For example, shipments of individual garments may not fit in a few containers, but they can be assembled and shipped with leather, auto and motorcycle parts, so the cost is reduced. "

Dongguan's manufacturing industry is the same, the jurisdiction of 32 towns around some core enterprises gathered into specific industrial clusters, forming a "one town, one product" characteristics. The city of Dalingshan, where Zeng worked as a furniture maker, is known as "the first town in China to export furniture" . A former employee of a state-owned enterprise in Jiangxi, Zeng first worked as a fitness equipment maker in the 1990s before moving to Dalingshan in 2003. "It's closer to the customers and cheaper, " said Zeng, adding that the wooden furniture has at least five or six processes that need to be coordinated with upstream and downstream companies.

The system of the upstream and downstream industrial chain, but also caused a longer return cycle of funds. And catering, tourism and other existing service industries, manufacturing and other industries more cash flow. An order can take as little as 90 to 120 days, or as long as 1 to 2 years, from the time the raw materials are purchased to the time the customer pays the bill, Zeng said. Li Boqin said that the clothing industry's fund withdrawal rate according to the quarter, "at least three months" , foreign trade process may be as long as four to six months.

As the basis of various industries, the logistics industry is also the same. In the fight against the epidemic, Lu and his colleagues helped organize the transportation of some medical supplies, and many businesses said they were short of cash and could not pay the freight for the time being. "The profit margin of the logistics industry is very thin. The average gross margin may be 3% to 5% . It is necessary to generate profits through high turnover, so once the turnover slows down, the impact is very big, " said Lu, logistics enterprises will always have at least 3 months of capital cushion inside, and fixed assets consumption is greater, "a little attention to the cash flow on the break. ".

Kaijing technology founder Zhang Shiwei is a student at Lakeside University. On Feb. 7, the head teacher of Hupan University called on students to discuss the resumption plan on Wechat. Students from all walks of life reached a consensus during the discussion: If we want to resume work, we must let the supply chain flow first, and the logistics industry must first resume work, "If the logistics industry does not return to work, the entire supply chain can not flow, the economy can not function. ". At the end of January, the company began preparations to resume work.

New Baptism of the trade

▲▲▲

New Baptism of the trade

The resumption of the real industry needs the support of human resources and supply chain, while the restart of the Internet industry needs a network with a large capacity. Most Internet companies started off working from home, but got off to a rocky start.

"first the enterprise wechat crashed, then the tencent conference crashed, then nail, still crashed. " The head of an Internet company in Chengdu said that it was very difficult to work online because there were too many online users, many software platform servers are initially difficult to load, often off-line meetings, and difficult to monitor, efficiency may be only the usual 70% ~ 80% . "sometimes there is no sound as we speak, so we invent some code words and hand gestures to communicate. "

On Feb. 17, more than 200 people were at Keating's headquarters, 70 percent of whom began work on a large scale and 30 percent worked from home, more than most Internet companies at the time. Because of the instability of the online meeting, we try to shorten the meeting time. "meetings can normally start as early as two hours, but now it's impossible for such a long time, and in a sense it has also improved our efficiency, " Lu said.

At the beginning of the company's resumption of work, according to the special situation during the epidemic, the company urgently developed "contactless freight service" , that is, logistics enterprises and drivers can pick up goods, deliver goods, GPS positioning, etc. on the APP, when the finished goods can be confirmed by electronic return order online, to replace the traditional paper return order, and then complete online payment, forming a closed loop. This prevents contact between the driver and others during loading and unloading and reduces the risk of infection. "In many places in Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Shanghai, drivers have to be isolated for 14 days even if they return from a trip, " Lu said.

The payment model has also been updated to current account. "Now is a special case, every single day of confirmation, the same day to do business settlement. " Lu Yang said, this can improve the enthusiasm of logistics enterprises, the speed of capital flow to do faster. "The upstream manufacturing industry, consumer goods industry and so on, they are also short of people to do logistics and are willing to shorten the payment cycle, so we urgently improved the model. " In addition, many drivers can not return to work temporarily because of the closure of the village, some logistics enterprises in order to normal operation, special period began to recruit a large number of external individual drivers, the latter is also more willing to per transport business settlement costs.

This is an attempt by Internet companies to use technology to address the pain points during the resumption of construction. Lu Yang said that the logistics industry itself has been a low degree of information, financial transparency, management is not standardized and other issues, to a certain extent, resulting in high logistics costs. To this end, they use scientific and technological means to explore its transformation, the introduction of Saas Systems, building platforms, using algorithms and data for logistics companies to match sources, and so on, trying to carry out information and digital reform of the industry. "Part of the logistics companies due to the lack of digital foundation of information, accounting is not accurate. We met the boss of a big logistics company with annual revenue of over 100 million yuan. He didn't know how much his vehicles cost in fixed assets and how much his accounts make or break each year,"said Lu, many bosses only know that they seem to make a lot of money, but in fact use information system management, will find that there will be a loss every year.

In a sense, many manufacturing smes have similar problems. Ceng Wuxiang admitted that he is not familiar with many detailed account expenditure, "this has to ask accounting" , there is no means of information management. Its trading model remains one based on trust between people rather than on technology and data. "We have a very extensive administration. "

While Internet companies are using technology to deal with the epidemic, manufacturing entrepreneurs are worrying about how their employees will come back, thinking "people are the most important thing. ". Lee says he has had a number of longtime employees since 2008, most with at least five years of service. In the field of high-end apparel production, manual skills are indispensable, the skills of workers have very high requirements. "there is a certain unique skill and technique in sewing clothes. Practice makes perfect. The longer you do it, the more stable it becomes. It takes time to settle down, " said Li Boqin, adding that many garment companies felt passive as the Wenzhou epidemic prevented workers from returning home, "It's going to take a lot of time to retrain these workers. ".

"As long as people are around, everything is easy to say. The human factor is more urgent, " said Li Boqin, adding that the focus of the current business is to protect at all costs. Wenzhou is the most affected area outside Hubei, where the government is in charge of the outside and entrepreneurs control the inside. Li Boqin's factory area is now eliminated every day, the staff as far as possible does not let go out, in the factory self-isolation. He monitors the health of employees outside the home every day, urging them to read more and spend time with their families, and giving advance payments to employees who are struggling with mortgage payments and car payments.

Li Boqin said he could not afford to lose his business due to the outbreak of the disease, "even if it is possible to lose everything. ". "If I had an outbreak, the client would think it was a dangerous company and the staff wouldn't come back, even if I had a eleven million per cent capital reserve, " he said, it doesn't matter if the machine is not there, it doesn't matter if the factory is closed, you can open a new company, "as long as people are there. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
According to Li, the company is on a roll until 2018, and the outbreak has given them a chance to reflect and change, to explore new products and markets, and form new growth points. "The crisis is really about breaking down some of what we thought was a success and re-establishing a set of balances. That's what we as business owners have to think about. "

At present, in Zhejiang, Shanghai and other places, through the "health code" , reworkers have adopted the preparation system, that is, through a real-time dynamic qr code developed urgently by Internet companies, that is to know whether the health code applicant and confirmed or suspected cases of shared transport, whether from the focus of epidemic areas, and so on. This is what makes Li Boqin feel gratified, so the project must only be supported by the government in order to start by the Internet large enterprises, small and medium enterprises can not do.

And for some Internet companies, high growth expectations will have to come down. Lu said that after initially seeing the bleak state of the logistics industry under the epidemic, investors organized online meetings several times to help them recommend resources to tide over the difficulties. They also set annual cost reduction plans, human resources structure optimization plans and key market development strategy, and so on, the original business doubling target, may be reduced to increase by 50% . "The business unit has to be as small as possible, and then in the smallest business unit, we have to encourage the ability of the team to form a minimum profit unit. We would give more incentive to make a profit in this area, but if the unit is still in a high-investment burn condition, we would definitely shut it down."

Through this outbreak, they also have more exploration in digital communication and office means, feel that the future must insist on implementation. "Quantitative assessment can be done more precisely, because people are not in front of you after all, " Lu said. "The epidemic is also an opportunity to just sort out the entire structure and model of the enterprise more clearly. "
